  You do not need a visa if you’re staying up to 6 months
<% end %>

<% govspeak_for :body do %>
  You can stay in the UK for up to 6 months without a visa.

  However, you should bring the [same documents](/government/publications/visitor-visa-guide-to-supporting-documents) you’d need to apply for a visa, to show to officers at the UK border.

  %If you have a criminal record or you’ve previously been refused entry into the UK, you may want to [apply for a visa](/browse/visas-immigration/short-visit-visas).%

  ##If you’re staying more than 6 months

  You can apply for a [Parent of a Child Student visa](/parent-of-a-child-at-school-visa) if your child is under 12 and at an independent day school.
<% end %>
